1
00:00:00,030 --> 00:00:01,360
In Chinese,

2
00:00:01,830 --> 00:00:03,210
the same sentiment

3
00:00:03,280 --> 00:00:06,570
can be interpreted differently by different people.

4
00:00:07,660 --> 00:00:10,160
Take Su Shi's "Jiang Cheng Zi" as an example:

5
00:00:10,490 --> 00:00:14,530
"The distant lonely grave a thousand miles away; there is no place to express the sorrow and desolation in my heart.

6
00:00:14,530 --> 00:00:17,470
Even if we were to meet again, you wouldn't recognize me.

7
00:00:17,470 --> 00:00:20,530
I am now covered in dust, and my temples are like frost."

8
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:24,830
This conveys the sorrow that, after enduring the vicissitudes of time,

9
00:00:24,830 --> 00:00:26,030
when they meet again,

10
00:00:26,930 --> 00:00:29,410
they have already been separated by death.

11
00:00:30,620 --> 00:00:31,620
Everyone,

12
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:33,740
can you understand?

13
00:00:37,740 --> 00:00:38,480
It's okay.

14
00:00:40,950 --> 00:00:42,370
"The reuniting of a broken mirror."

15
00:00:42,370 --> 00:00:44,630
You should have heard this idiom, right?

16
00:00:45,190 --> 00:00:46,120
Yes.

17
00:00:46,150 --> 00:00:46,710
Okay.

18
00:00:47,290 --> 00:00:49,850
Do you know its origin and meaning?

19
00:00:55,350 --> 00:00:56,350
Jiang Tian.

20
00:00:57,830 --> 00:01:00,250
Come on, let me test you.

21
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:07,560
This is the true story of Princess Lechang of the Southern Dynasties.

22
00:01:08,230 --> 00:01:10,430
She was forced to part from her husband.

23
00:01:11,910 --> 00:01:14,310
Before they separated, they broke a mirror

24
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,539
and each took half.

25
00:01:18,930 --> 00:01:20,400
Many years later,

26
00:01:21,590 --> 00:01:23,590
they reunited because of the mirror

27
00:01:24,390 --> 00:01:26,789
and spent the rest of their lives together.

28
00:01:31,830 --> 00:01:34,080
However, behind this beautiful story

29
00:01:36,210 --> 00:01:37,770
lies a deeper meaning.

30
00:01:42,490 --> 00:01:43,620
You're home.

31
00:01:50,539 --> 00:01:51,580
Welcome home.

32
00:01:56,960 --> 00:01:59,690
During the decades they could not see each other,

33
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,060
they could only look at the mirror

34
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:08,330
and long for the beautiful image of each other.

35
00:02:12,410 --> 00:02:13,670
After their reunion,

36
00:02:14,460 --> 00:02:15,440
in the mirror,

37
00:02:19,329 --> 00:02:23,060
I could no longer see your enchanting face like a fairy from before,

38
00:02:24,530 --> 00:02:26,820
only the desolate moonlight

39
00:02:30,290 --> 00:02:32,150
reflected by the passage of time.

40
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:45,740
[The On1y One]

41
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:48,700
[Episode 11, Kissing: It was Just Four Lips Touching Each Other]

42
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,240
Last night,

43
00:04:16,540 --> 00:04:18,120
I slept like this?

44
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,990
How is that possible? I'm not dead.

45
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,200
Oh, right.

46
00:04:26,660 --> 00:04:29,220
Mr. Sun...

47
00:04:31,620 --> 00:04:32,450
Damn!

48
00:04:32,909 --> 00:04:34,000
Who put the ball here?

49
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:34,930
What's going on?

50
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:36,760
Hey.

51
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:38,090
It wasn't me.

52
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:44,430
What are you doing?

53
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:45,650
There are so many beds here.

54
00:04:45,650 --> 00:04:47,380
Why are you sleeping together?

55
00:04:51,030 --> 00:04:51,940
Well...

56
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:54,440
Didn't you guys just go home yesterday?

57
00:04:55,090 --> 00:04:56,620
Why did you come back today?

58
00:04:57,770 --> 00:04:59,890
The practice exam is coming up, right?

59
00:04:59,890 --> 00:05:01,390
So, Shi and I thought

60
00:05:01,570 --> 00:05:03,980
we'd review together

61
00:05:03,990 --> 00:05:06,720
while the two top students are in the dorm, right?

62
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:08,130
No.

63
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:09,790
That's not the point now.

64
00:05:09,790 --> 00:05:10,750
The point now is...

65
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:13,710
The point is that a thief came in last night, you know?

66
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:15,940
A thief?

67
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,300
Oh, right.

68
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,040
When I got back just now, I heard people from Room 308 talking.

69
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,260
The whole floor was burglarized.

70
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:24,780
And I think I even saw someone.

71
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:26,320
Someone?

72
00:05:26,350 --> 00:05:27,700
Yeah, just a blurry figure.

73
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:29,660
I'm not sure if it was a person or a ghost.

74
00:05:29,660 --> 00:05:30,280
A ghost?

75
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:34,080
Come on, Gao.

76
00:05:34,610 --> 00:05:35,460
Did they catch it?

77
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:36,800
Was it a thief or a ghost?

78
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:38,610
How could it be caught so quickly?

79
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:40,490
The police were only called last night.

80
00:05:40,490 --> 00:05:42,460
But the dormitory supervisor told us

81
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:45,330
to be extra cautious these days and,

82
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:48,490
if possible, to sleep in the same room or share beds

83
00:05:49,060 --> 00:05:50,520
to look out for each other.

84
00:05:52,140 --> 00:05:52,800
Shi,

85
00:05:53,690 --> 00:05:54,860
let's share a bed.

86
00:05:55,740 --> 00:05:56,550
Stop joking.

87
00:05:56,580 --> 00:05:58,040
This is serious. There's a ghost.

88
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,050
No!

89
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:00,290
I'm really scared.

90
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,200
I'm more scared of you.

91
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,210
I'll kneel. I'm begging you.

92
00:06:03,210 --> 00:06:03,870
Gao Tianyang.

93
00:06:03,870 --> 00:06:05,220
Just agree to him.

94
00:06:05,310 --> 00:06:06,180
Have you heard?

95
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,920
There was a thief in the boys' dorm last night.

96
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,000
Really?

97
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,250
That's not true.

98
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,120
I heard that in the middle of the night,

99
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,220
a shadow suddenly appeared.

100
00:06:14,220 --> 00:06:15,620
The dormitory supervisor was afraid that people would panic,

101
00:06:15,620 --> 00:06:16,460
so he said there was a thief.

102
00:06:16,460 --> 00:06:19,790
No wonder I often hear someone crying in the middle of the night.

103
00:06:19,790 --> 00:06:20,830
Then let's sleep together.

104
00:06:20,830 --> 00:06:22,030
Okay, let's sleep together.

105
00:06:22,030 --> 00:06:23,050
I'm scared.

106
00:06:23,620 --> 00:06:25,280
I don't want to be the last one!

107
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,940
Get up.

108
00:07:23,830 --> 00:07:24,760
It's morning.

109
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:26,950
Darn it.

110
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:31,750
I didn't sleep all night because of your snoring.

111
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:32,690
Come on.

112
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,909
They haven't caught the thief yet.

113
00:07:34,909 --> 00:07:36,920
I'll sleep on the upper bunk when they do,

114
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:37,710
right?

115
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:39,090
Morning.

116
00:07:39,330 --> 00:07:40,120
Morning.

117
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:41,110
Morning.

118
00:07:42,110 --> 00:07:45,560
I didn't expect that sharing beds would become a trend.

119
00:07:46,380 --> 00:07:47,490
How dare you say that?

120
00:07:47,490 --> 00:07:48,810
Aren't you two the same?

121
00:07:48,810 --> 00:07:50,170
I'm not.

122
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:51,610
I'm going back soon.

123
00:07:52,580 --> 00:07:54,680
The doctor said my foot is healed,

124
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,960
so I can go back to the upper bunk to sleep.

125
00:07:57,990 --> 00:07:58,740
It stinks.

126
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:00,580
I just changed it yesterday.

127
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:01,380
Alright then.

128
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,980
I'm going to the bathroom.

129
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:11,430
Or are you afraid

130
00:08:11,580 --> 00:08:13,110
and want me to stay with you?

131
00:08:14,950 --> 00:08:15,810
Whatever.

132
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:16,960
Whatever?

133
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:17,960
So casual?

134
00:08:18,910 --> 00:08:19,930
I'm not.

135
00:08:20,410 --> 00:08:21,250
I'll go up now.

136
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,070
I'm going back.

137
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:30,210
Hello, long time no see.

138
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:36,990
Sheng Wang.

139
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:37,880
Yes?

140
00:08:40,030 --> 00:08:40,870
What's wrong with you?

141
00:08:40,870 --> 00:08:41,770
Tian,

142
00:08:41,890 --> 00:08:43,360
you've become naughty.

143
00:08:43,820 --> 00:08:44,480
Really?

144
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,290
You don't think so?

145
00:08:50,290 --> 00:08:51,120
Darn it!

146
00:08:51,210 --> 00:08:52,050
Why so sudden?

147
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:54,700
Shi Yu, are you done?

148
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,860
Cut it and let me use the bathroom first.

149
00:08:58,220 --> 00:08:59,040
Damn.

150
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:04,710
Attention, everyone.

151
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:06,840
Lastly, I have a few things to tell you.

152
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:09,000
First, I'm sure you've heard that this time,

153
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,400
the practice exam will follow the new class division system.

154
00:09:12,790 --> 00:09:13,450
In the past,

155
00:09:13,450 --> 00:09:17,040
only the bottom three students in the exam would leave this class.

156
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,130
But this time,

157
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:19,490
it won't be that easy.

158
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:20,340
So, Jing,

159
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,490
what's the new rule?

160
00:09:22,090 --> 00:09:24,020
The new class division rule is that

161
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:26,020
your class will keep 30 students.

162
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:27,850
If you rank in the top 30,

163
00:09:27,870 --> 00:09:29,220
you can stay in Class A.

164
00:09:29,410 --> 00:09:32,740
Those ranked after 30 will be transferred to other classes.

165
00:09:35,210 --> 00:09:36,470
Quiet.

166
00:09:36,620 --> 00:09:38,590
Don't get too excited.

167
00:09:40,410 --> 00:09:41,540
Yeah.

168
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:44,980
We're so excited that we're almost dying.

169
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:47,220
Xu Tianshu.

170
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,050
Yes! Jing.

171
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:51,420
At least you can stay alive until I finish talking, right?

172
00:09:51,420 --> 00:09:52,510
No problem, Jing.

173
00:09:54,650 --> 00:09:56,680
If you don't want to fail this time

174
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:58,160
and want to stay in Class A,

175
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:01,130
the upcoming period is crucial.

176
00:10:01,830 --> 00:10:03,290
Students in the front row,

177
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:05,780
come up and get today's English exam papers.

178
00:10:06,740 --> 00:10:08,130
From today on,

179
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:10,840
there will be an extra exam paper every day.

180
00:10:17,790 --> 00:10:18,790
Damn. I'm doomed.

181
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:20,450
I used to be the lucky fourth-to-last.

182
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:22,870
Now I'm straight into the elimination zone.

183
00:10:22,870 --> 00:10:23,920
Oh, don't say that.

184
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:25,160
I'm in the elimination zone too.

185
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:26,040
You're not in the elimination zone.

186
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:27,220
You're just passing by, okay?

187
00:10:27,220 --> 00:10:28,030
Tell me,

188
00:10:28,410 --> 00:10:29,380
since the first day you've been here,

189
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:31,930
is there even one exam you didn't score incredibly high in?

190
00:10:31,930 --> 00:10:33,080
I haven't taken an exam for so long because of my foot injury.

191
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,140
I'm not in the zone.

192
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,660
I'm not just passing by.

193
00:10:35,660 --> 00:10:36,270
It's okay.

194
00:10:36,330 --> 00:10:37,150
If you transfer to another class,

195
00:10:37,150 --> 00:10:38,410
I'll keep you company.

196
00:10:38,460 --> 00:10:39,110
Sure.

197
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:44,630
I'm just kidding.

198
00:10:44,630 --> 00:10:46,760
I'll find someone to keep you company.

199
00:10:47,950 --> 00:10:51,020
There's another announcement to make.

200
00:10:51,580 --> 00:10:53,480
As you all know, last time,

201
00:10:53,510 --> 00:10:57,710
Li Yu, Qi Jiahao, Sheng Wang, and Jiang Tian from our class

202
00:10:58,120 --> 00:11:00,970
represented the school in the citywide English competition.

203
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:02,450
The results are now out.

204
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,330
Did you guys not do well?

205
00:11:04,490 --> 00:11:05,330
I don't know.

206
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:08,590
You and Tian are probably the most likely to win.

207
00:11:08,590 --> 00:11:10,620
-Here are two certificates.
-Didn't Jing tell you anything?

208
00:11:10,620 --> 00:11:12,610
-One is the second prize and the other is the first prize.
-She did.

209
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:13,400
We turned in our papers early.

210
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,790
-Take a guess,
